The sophists predate the classical philosophers, but theirs was mostly an oral tradition; Socrates despised them because he viewed them as manipulative, using dogma, emotion, and loaded rhetoric to pass on their knowledge. It's not that they weren't legitimately teaching their pupils; think of it like the Buddhist tradition, where those who attain Enlightenment are never allowed to explain it. If you hate that concept, Socrates held the sophists in contempt for similar reasons.
